}
```

Since `runPipeline()` never sets state to "running", `bake.stateSnapshot.status` stays as whatever it was before (probably "idle" from reset or "done" from a prior run). So the guard check of `status === "running"` will ALWAYS be false, meaning it never prevents concurrent runs!

But wait - is this actually the old behavior too? Let me check the old version of `runPipeline()`...

I can't see the old version directly, but the diff shows the old `start.ts` was:
